{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove the right to withdraw from RE lessons in schools",
        "additional_details": "I believe removing the right for parents to withdraw their child from RE lessons will ensure that students have a basic knowledge and understanding of all the faiths that our society, and the wider world, have.\r\n \r\nIf creating a diverse, tolerant and peaceful society is desired, surely we have the obligation to ensure that all children learn about all faiths.",
        "background": "Some students only stay in RE lessons when their own faith is being taught. \r\n \r\nI feel that this is against the spirit of inclusion and may cause division, resentment and ignorance.",
